OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FAs a consensus bubbled up that the
OL,7,FHolyrood election campaign was rather
OL,8,Ftepid, the SNP believed voters were
OL,9,Fquietly warming to John Swinney.
OL,11,FIt is part of a four-part strategy
OL,12,Fthat the first minister has
OL,13,Fimplemented since his party was
OL,14,Fwalloped almost two years ago at the
OL,15,FUK general election.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FHis most senior allies privately
OL,7,Flikened it to "boiling a frog" and
OL,8,Fpointed out just days before people
OL,9,Fcast their ballots that Mr Swinney was
OL,10,Foutpolling the party on positive
OL,11,Fratings.
OL,13,F"People haven't realised the
OL,14,Ftemperature has gone from really cool
OL,15,Ftowards us to being really quite warm
OL,16,Ftowards us," said one.
OL,26,@oD@OOUoD@^O]uD@AOUxD@LO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
