FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FIt also looked daft when the SNP
OL,7,Fleader saw a US number flash on his
OL,8,Fmobile phone when he was in a garden
OL,9,Fcentre in Kirkintilloch, just outside
OL,10,FGlasgow, and answered to speak to
OL,11,FPresident Trump.
OL,13,FHis party then published the personal
OL,14,Fnote they had kept in their back
OL,15,Fpocket alongside the fact of the phone
OL,16,Fcall.
OL,18,F"This should have been a day where
OL,19,Feveryone did their own thing and tried
OL,20,Fto take credit," said one senior SNP
OL,21,Fsource.
OL,26,@zD@AOU|D@PO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,F"But (Scottish Secretary and Labour
OL,7,Fcampaign co-ordinator) Douglas
OL,8,FAlexander and (Scottish Labour leader)
OL,9,FAnas Sarwar did their petty ****
OL,10,Finstead and looked stupid."
OL,12,FThe episode also illustrated a marked
OL,13,Fdifference in approach from Mr Swinney
OL,14,Fcompared to his predecessors.
OL,16,FIn 2018, then First Minister Nicola
OL,17,FSturgeon led a Pride parade in Glasgow
OL,18,Fin support of LGBT equality when
OL,19,FPresident Trump visited Scotland.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@FpmoD@VpnpD@OpmpD@fpnrD@[O]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FIn contrast, Mr Swinney held
OL,7,Fdiscussions with him during his trip
OL,8,Flast summer before flying across the
OL,9,FAtlantic and he has repeatedly refused
OL,10,Fto take potshots against the man
OL,11,Foccupying the White House when teed up
OL,12,Fby the likes of the Scottish Greens.
OL,14,F"People talk about John being cautious
OL,15,Fbut he knows when to gamble," said one
OL,16,Fsenior figure.
OL,18,F"He took a risk at every stage (by
OL,19,Fmeeting with President Trump) and it
OL,20,Fpaid off a week before the election."
OL,26,@vD@AOUwD@]O]zD@AOUzD@`pm{D@]pn|D@eO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FThe current warmth from Washington
OL,7,Falso saw the president post a public
OL,8,Fmessage congratulating Mr Swinney on
OL,9,Fhis "big electoral victory" once the
OL,10,Fballots had been counted.
OL,12,FIt was far from plain sailing for the
OL,13,FSNP, though.
OL,15,FThe campaign started and ended with
OL,16,Fthe conviction then sentencing of
OL,17,FJordan Linden, a former nationalist
OL,18,Fcouncil leader who was jailed for 18
OL,19,Fmonths after being found guilty of
OL,20,Fsexual offences against young men and
OL,21,Fteenagers as young as 14.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G12/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FOpponents latched onto that with the
OL,7,Fparty slow to react to early criticism.
OL,9,FMr Swinney was also less than sure-
OL,10,Ffooted in the first televised election
OL,11,Fdebate on the BBC when blows were
OL,12,Flanded by audience members ` and Mr
OL,13,FSarwar ` on the NHS.
OL,15,FOne opposition leader privately mocked
OL,16,Fthe first minister pulling a
OL,17,F"crumpled" yellow page of notes from
OL,18,Fhis inside jacket pocket just before
OL,19,Fthat event started and claimed it was
OL,20,Fa sign he was struggling.
OL,26,@yD@AOUyD@JO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G13/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FBut Mr Swinney was comfortable if far
OL,7,Ffrom sparkling in the Channel 4 and
OL,8,FSTV debates and was said to be
OL,9,Fparticularly pleased at having "done
OL,10,Fup Alex Cole-Hamilton like a kipper"
OL,11,Fin the latter by boxing the Scottish
OL,12,FLiberal Democrat leader into agreeing
OL,13,Fthat SNP budgets had delivered
OL,14,Fpositively for the country.
OL,16,FHe was, though, uncomfortable when
OL,17,Fquestioned on his failure to meet his
OL,18,Fown self-imposed target of having no
OL,19,Fone in Scotland wait more than a year
OL,20,Ffor NHS treatment by April.
OL,26,@qD@`OUrD@dO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G14/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35515
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FBizarrely, opponents failed to punch
OL,7,Fthat bruise when it would have
OL,8,Fparticularly hurt the SNP leader's
OL,9,Fconfidence at least.
OL,11,FIt would have stung because it was a
OL,12,Fkey part of his four-stage recovery
OL,13,Fprocess for the party, which was
OL,14,Fdevised in the wake of their general
OL,15,Felection drubbing.
OL,17,FStage one was to win the right to be
OL,18,Fheard by the public.
OL,20,FStage two was to rebuild trust and
OL,21,Fdeliver something.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G15/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35516
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,F"We had an equation: Hope + Delivery =
OL,7,FTrust," said one person involved in
OL,8,Fthe planning.
OL,10,FAbolishing peak rail fares ended up
OL,11,Fbeing the flagship for this because it
OL,12,Fwas easy to understand.
OL,14,FBut the party had a missed target that
OL,15,Fopponents could have highlighted to
OL,16,Fundermine this plank of the strategy.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G16/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35517
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FStage three was about vision, which Mr
OL,7,FSwinney believes he set out with his
OL,8,Fpathway to an independence referendum
OL,9,Fand election pledges such as GP walk
OL,10,Fin centres.
OL,12,FStage four was simple: get out the
OL,13,Fvote.
OL,15,FThey managed that even if they failed
OL,16,Fto meet their stated aim of a majority.
OL,18,FThis was in no small part down to a
OL,19,Frevamped campaigning system that saw
OL,20,F3,500 people spoken with every day
OL,21,Fduring the campaign.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G17/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35518
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FSenior figures in the SNP leadership
OL,7,Fwere "horrified by what we discovered"
OL,8,Fabout the campaign operation in last
OL,9,Fyear's Hamilton, Larkhall and
OL,10,FStonehouse byelection.
OL,12,FThe party's headquarters was
OL,13,Foverhauled with former MP and special
OL,14,Fadviser Callum McCaig appointed as
OL,15,Fchief executive in what is seen
OL,16,Finternally as a significant move.
OL,18,FPart of this was a relentless focus on
OL,19,FScotland's 73 constituencies with the
OL,20,Fnationalists needing to win 65 seats
OL,21,Fto secure that Holyrood majority.
OL,26,@oD@FOUoD@fO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G18/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35519
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,F"We can afford to lose no more than
OL,7,Feight (seats)," said one strategist in
OL,8,Fthe days before the vote.
OL,10,F"We can afford to lose no more than
OL,11,Feight. We don't work to a figure of
OL,12,F65. We work to a figure of eight."
OL,14,FIn the end they lost almost double
OL,15,Fthat even though their internal data
OL,16,Fwas projecting an SNP majority at
OL,17,FHolyrood when it was run through the
OL,18,Fmost pessimistic modelling during the
OL,19,Ffinal week of campaigning.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@GpmoD@MpnoD@OO]rD@AOUtD@bO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G19/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35520
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FIndeed the party lost support in many
OL,7,Fseats even as they claimed victory.
OL,9,FThere was, for some in the SNP, an
OL,10,Funcomfortable optimism towards the end
OL,11,Fof the campaign.
OL,13,FOn the final weekend before going to
OL,14,Fthe polls, the senior team held one of
OL,15,Fits daily 8am meetings to analyse what
OL,16,Fthey saw as potential problems or
OL,17,Fnegative stories that day.
OL,19,F"We realised we didn't have any," said
OL,20,Fone person on the call.
OL,26,@{D@AOU{D@aO]
