OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FThis was in part fuelled by a small
OL,7,Fpolling bump over the last two years
OL,8,Ffrom low 30% to winning 38% of
OL,9,Fconstituency votes at the election.
OL,11,FIt led to one aide to mix animal
OL,12,Fmetaphors by comparing Mr Swinney to
OL,13,Fthe victorious character in Aesop's
OL,14,Ffable of the tortoise and the hare.
OL,16,F"The tortoise is winning the race,"
OL,17,Fthe source said. "Anas is the hare but
OL,18,Fthe tortoise ****ing wins."
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@cO]yD@ROUzD@[O]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G21/57
