PN,35526
SC,0026
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FScottish leader Malcolm Offord was
OL,7,Fstopped in the street by workmen in
OL,8,FStranraer, who asked him for a selfie,
OL,9,Fafter beIng interviewed by ITV Border
OL,10,Fwith the party taking that as another
OL,11,Fpositive sign for their chances.
OL,13,FActivists were also bussed up from
OL,14,FCarlisle to help campaign in
OL,15,Fneighbouring Dumfriesshire as the
OL,16,Fparty looked for a win there.
OL,18,FNone of it translated into the
OL,19,Fconstituency performances they hoped
OL,20,Ffor in the south of Scotland.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G26/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35527
SC,0027
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FIt was Mr Offord's performances in
OL,7,Ftelevised debates that sparked the
OL,8,Fcampaign into life on two occasions.
OL,10,FFirst, when Mr Sarwar was chastising
OL,11,Fhim for Ms Beresford's online posts,
OL,12,FMr Offord claimed the Scottish Labour
OL,13,Fleader had suggested the pair work
OL,14,Ftogether to remove the SNP.
OL,16,FThe aggressive nature of Mr Sarwar's
OL,17,Fattacks had been riling Reform for a
OL,18,Fwhile and just hours before the
OL,19,FChannel 4 dust up, they had laid the
OL,20,Fgroundwork for the move in an
OL,21,Finterview with the Scotsman newspaper.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G27/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35528
SC,0028
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FOne witness at the debate believed the
OL,7,Fmove was pre-planned, adding: "No-one
OL,8,Freally noticed that Reform folk
OL,9,Fcheered when he (Mr Offord) said it -
OL,10,Fso they've been weighing it up for a
OL,11,Fwhile, I reckon."
OL,13,FThe central claim was flatly denied by
OL,14,FMr Sarwar, who went on to later allege
OL,15,Fthat Reform's marquee MSP defector
OL,16,FGraham Simpson had privately
OL,17,Fcriticised Mr Offord and called Mr
OL,18,FKerr a "weasel".
OL,26,@oD@_OUqD@QpmqD@[pnsD@QO]zD@HOUzD@OO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G28/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35529
SC,0029
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FMr Simpson denied this, instead
OL,7,Finsisting he sees Mr Kerr as a lion,
OL,8,Fbut there were some internal
OL,9,Fgrumblings about his apparent
OL,10,Fambitions and Mr Offord's performance
OL,11,Fduring the campaign.
OL,13,F"He's not well liked," said one Reform
OL,14,Fsource of Mr Kerr. "He's the kind of
OL,15,Fguy we're trying to keep out of
OL,16,Fpolitics."
OL,18,FDuring the final televised debate on
OL,19,FSTV, Mr Offord raised eyebrows once
OL,20,Fagain with his boast that he owns "six
OL,21,Fhouses, five cars and six boats".
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@VO]vD@TOUxD@JO]|D@cOU}D@`O]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G29/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
