OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FThat's 17 big ticket items. He's now
OL,7,Fwon exactly the same number of MSPs.
OL,9,FOne message came consistently
OL,10,Fthroughout the campaign from anyone
OL,11,Fsenior in Labour's election campaign:
OL,12,Fthe polls are wrong.
OL,14,FIn fact the number crunchers were
OL,15,Fright and Mr Sawrar spectacularly
OL,16,Fmissed the mark.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G30/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35531
SC,0031
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FThe defiant message had come
OL,7,Fconsistently from the first week of
OL,8,Fthe campaign with sources claiming
OL,9,Ffeedback from canvassers suggested
OL,10,Fundecided voters were breaking for
OL,11,FLabour and support for the SNP and
OL,12,FReform was not as high as the publicly
OL,13,Fstated 35% and 20%.
OL,15,FThis briefing continued through to the
OL,16,Fparty's manifesto launch, which was a
OL,17,Fslick event although with no new eye-
OL,18,Fcatching policy in a move that both
OL,19,Fsurprised and relieved the SNP.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G31/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35532
SC,0032
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FThe choice not to hold anything back
OL,7,Fon the day was deliberate, according
OL,8,Fto those close to the process.
OL,10,FBut it meant there wasn't much for the
OL,11,Fmedia to focus on and Mr Sarwar
OL,12,Fappeared irritated when questions
OL,13,Falmost inevitably drifted back to Sir
OL,14,FKeir Starmer and the UK Government.
OL,16,FNevertheless, those analysing data in
OL,17,Fthe party projected confidence as they
OL,18,Fsaid internal data said they were
OL,19,Fincreasing their "retention rates" of
OL,20,Fvoters in target seats.
OL,26,@{D@ROU{D@bO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G32/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35533
SC,0033
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FNot everyone was so positive.
OL,8,FOne parliamentarian said that while
OL,9,Fthey agreed the polls were
OL,10,Funderestimating Labour it was "not by
OL,11,Fnearly as much as needed".
OL,13,FThey added: "I think Anas's team have
OL,14,Fscrewed up large parts of the campaign
OL,15,Fas well in their rush to blame the UK
OL,16,Fgovernment."
OL,18,FIt was a big call by Mr Sarwar to call
OL,19,Ffor Sir Keir to quit as Prime Minister
OL,20,Fthree months out from the election.
OL,26,@rD@_OUsD@YO]uD@MOUxD@LO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G33/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35534
SC,0034
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FCandidates said it made it easier to
OL,7,Fget past the difficult conversations
OL,8,Fon the door with people furious at the
OL,9,Fparty's performance in Westminster.
OL,11,FBut it created tension between the
OL,12,FScottish leader and the Scottish
OL,13,Fsecretary, who was also co-chairing
OL,14,Fthe election campaign.
OL,16,FTwo sources said the relationship
OL,17,Fbetween Mr Sarwar and Mr Alexander was
OL,18,F"difficult".
OL,26,@zD@AOUzD@KO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G34/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35535
SC,0035
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FThis was vehemently denied by people
OL,7,Fat the top of the campaign, who said
OL,8,Fthere was no fall out between the
OL,9,Fpoliticians running the election
OL,10,Foperation.
OL,12,FBut there was another fundamental
OL,13,Fpoint that some found difficult on the
OL,14,Fdoorsteps: "Saying, 'Labour is *****,
OL,15,Fvote Labour' is not exactly
OL,16,Fcompelling."
OL,26,@vD@LOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G35/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35536
SC,0036
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FYet as scandals surrounding Lord
OL,7,FMandelson's appointment as US
OL,8,Fambassador continued to dominate
OL,9,Fheadlines, it was not difficult to
OL,10,Ffind people who believed Mr Sarwar had
OL,11,Fmade the only decision he could by
OL,12,Fcalling for Sir Keir's resignation.
OL,14,FMeanwhile, there were mixed messages
OL,15,Fcoming from Whitehall about what to do
OL,16,Fif the SNP won a majority and demanded
OL,17,Fa second independence referendum.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G36/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35537
SC,0037
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FSome were said to be "nervous" about
OL,7,Fthe prospect but others said there was
OL,8,Fgeneral agreement behind the publicly
OL,9,Fstated view of UK Health Secretary Wes
OL,10,FStreeting's bullish statement, based
OL,11,Fon Labour's general election manifesto
OL,12,Fpledge: "We're not having one."
OL,14,FIn the final days, Labour had
OL,15,Fprivately all but given up on winning
OL,16,Fpower despite throwing everything
OL,17,Fincluding the kitchen sink at the SNP.
OL,26,@nD@VOUnD@^O]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G37/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35538
SC,0038
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,FExperienced nationalists said this
OL,7,Ffailed to learn the lessons from the
OL,8,Flast time Labour won a Holyrood
OL,9,Felection: "We thought in 2003, 'Don't
OL,10,Fscare the horses, they are so **** the
OL,11,Fpublic will vote them out,' and we
OL,12,Flearned the hard way that we had to be
OL,13,Fpositive, in favour of something."
OL,15,FBy voting day, Labour had whittled
OL,16,Fdown its list of target constituencies
OL,17,Ffrom 38 to 33 but still believed it
OL,18,Fhad a path to victory. It only won
OL,19,Fthree.
OL,21,FCorrectly, not everyone was convinced.
OL,26,@qD@KOUuD@bO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G38/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,356,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35539
SC,0039
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,F"I think the SNP have largely failed
OL,7,Fto make this all about Starmer and
OL,8,Fwe've failed to make it all about
OL,9,Ftheir record in government," predicted
OL,10,Fa prescient source.
OL,12,F"Somehow the dynamics haven't
OL,13,Ffundamentally changed since 2021 so
OL,14,Fwe'll end up with a similar status quo
OL,15,Fresult. SNP will lose seats but
OL,16,Fprobably have a bigger lead over the
OL,17,Fsecond placed party."
OL,19,FOnly seven results had been declared
OL,20,Fwhen Mr Sarwar conceded the election.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@\O]tD@AOUyD@UO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G39/57
