PN,35540
SC,0040
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F355A1778508672
OL,3,CInside the metaphors and mess of the
OL,4,CHolyrood election campaign
OL,6,F"We made a big play and it didn't
OL,7,Fhappen," said a senior figure.
OL,9,F"But I don't think anyone in their
OL,10,Fright mind would lay the blame for the
OL,11,Flast two years of the failure of the
OL,12,FLabour Party at Anas Sarwar's door.
OL,14,F"We've got a party going through a
OL,15,Ftough time and going to hold it
OL,16,Ftogether."
OL,18,FSo Mr Sarwar is vowing to fight on.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@HO]qD@AOUvD@AOUxD@JO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G40/57
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
